---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About this place — Postcards from Far Away"
  activeNav="about"
  screenLabel="About"
  mastheadRight="About this place"
>
  <main class="page" style="padding-top: clamp(40px, 8vw, 120px); padding-bottom: 80px;">

    <section class="editorial-grid" style="align-items: end;">
      <div style="grid-column: 1 / span 8;">
        <div class="eyebrow fade-in">About this place</div>
        <h1 class="display fade-in-2" style="font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 5rem); margin: 18px 0 0; line-height: 0.98;">
          A reading room<br/>for <em>one engineer's</em><br/>intellectual life.
        </h1>
      </div>
      <div style="grid-column: 10 / span 3;" class="fade-in-3 meta">
        Edition 4<br/>
        Last revised May 28, 2026
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule rule-ink" style="margin: 64px 0 0;" />

    <section class="editorial-grid" style="margin-top: 64px; row-gap: 40px;">
      <figure style="grid-column: 1 / span 4;">
        <div class="thumb" style="aspect-ratio: 4/5;"><img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/portrait/800/1000" alt="Portrait placeholder." /></div>
      </figure>

      <div style="grid-column: 6 / span 7;">
        <p class="lede dropcap-none" style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.6rem; line-height: 1.4; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0 0 1em;">
          I am Praise Prince — an engineer by training, a reader by appetite, and a photographer by approximate accident.
        </p>

        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 17.5px; line-height: 1.65;">
          I keep this site the way some people keep a garden: it is not the point, exactly, but it is where the work of paying attention happens. Most of what I publish here is small. A photograph from a walk, a fragment overheard, a note on something in computer science or physics that struck me as more beautiful than it had any right to be. Once or twice a season, an essay — longer, slower, less sure of itself.
        </p>

        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 17.5px; line-height: 1.65;">
          I write between Lagos and Cambridge. I shoot mostly on a Yashica T4 my father gave me. I read more philosophy than is good for an engineer, and more code than is good for an essayist. The two halves do not always speak, but they share a room.
        </p>

        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 17.5px; line-height: 1.65;">
          This place is private without being secret. It has no analytics, no email capture, no newsletter form. You are simply here. <em>Thank you for that.</em>
        </p>

      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-glyph"></div>

    <section class="editorial-grid" style="row-gap: 56px;">

      <div style="grid-column: span 12;">
        <h2 class="display" style="font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.4rem); font-style: italic; margin: 0; color: var(--ink);">
          How this is put together.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div style="grid-column: span 4;">
        <div class="smallcaps" style="color: var(--ink-fade);">Typography</div>
        <hr class="rule" style="margin: 12px 0 16px;" />
        <dl style="margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.9;">
          <dt style="color: var(--ink-fade);">Display</dt>
          <dd style="margin: 0 0 8px; font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.4rem;">Instrument Serif</dd>
          <dt style="color: var(--ink-fade);">Reading</dt>
          <dd style="margin: 0 0 8px; font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1.2rem;">Newsreader, opsz</dd>
          <dt style="color: var(--ink-fade);">Interface</dt>
          <dd style="margin: 0 0 8px; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.95rem;">Geist</dd>
          <dt style="color: var(--ink-fade);">Metadata</dt>
          <dd style="margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85rem;">JetBrains Mono</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <div style="grid-column: span 4;">
        <div class="smallcaps" style="color: var(--ink-fade);">Code</div>
        <hr class="rule" style="margin: 12px 0 16px;" />
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0;">
          This is a small static site built with Astro. Most pages are Markdown files with frontmatter, because I wanted writing, photo rolls, walks, and notes to be easy to edit without turning the site into an app.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 12px 0 0;">
          The design leans on a few reusable tags and layouts rather than a CMS: essays, photos, walks, fragments, and desk entries each get just enough structure to stay organized while still feeling like a notebook.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 12px 0 0;">
          The code lives on <a href="https://github.com/praiseprince/blog" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);">GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="grid-column: span 6;">
        <div class="smallcaps" style="color: var(--ink-fade);">Elsewhere</div>
        <hr class="rule" style="margin: 12px 0 16px;" />
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.9;">
          <li>Email — <a href="mailto:praiseprince35@gmail.com" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);">praiseprince35@gmail.com</a></li>
          <li>Instagram — <a href="https://www.instagram.com/praiseprince_/" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);">praiseprince_</a></li>
          <li>GitHub — <a href="https://github.com/praiseprince" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);">praiseprince</a></li>
          <li>RSS feed — <a href="/feed.xml" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);">/feed.xml</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </section>

    <hr class="rule rule-ink" style="margin: 80px 0 24px;" />

    <p style="text-align: center; font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0;">
      "We owe it to the fields that our houses will not be the only things to stand in them." — W. Berry
    </p>
  </main>

  <style>
    @media (max-width: 800px) {
      .editorial-grid > div[style*="grid-column: 1 / span 8"],
      .editorial-grid > div[style*="grid-column: 10 / span 3"],
      .editorial-grid > figure[style*="grid-column: 1 / span 4"],
      .editorial-grid > div[style*="grid-column: 6 / span 7"],
      .editorial-grid > div[style*="grid-column: span 4"],
      .editorial-grid > div[style*="grid-column: span 6"],
      .editorial-grid > div[style*="grid-column: span 12"] {
        grid-column: 1 / -1 !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
